Text:
I've surveyed our surroundings. No signs of enemy
reinforcements.

Thank you, Epsilon. Considering their number of
casualties, including those that were part of the
diversion, I'm sure defending this facility is the
last thing on their minds.

Delta and Beta should be handling those who tried to
escape.
Ah...gahhhh...
Lady Alpha!

This one here is the only one still breathing.
As for the others...it seems we were too late.
Damn it...

We can grieve later. There's no time to waste—we must
save this one.
Of course, Lady Alpha! If you'll do the honors—
It's you who'll do the saving, Epsilon.
What?!

B-But, Lady Alpha, only you and Master Shadow have
ever cured the curse on the possessed—
And today, you'll join our ranks.
But I can't...

We, the Seven Shadows, have all trained in curing the
curse, but your control of magic is exceptional.

It's no exaggeration to say your talent exceeds mine
when it comes to your delicate, precise control of
magic.

I'm...honored. But I'm not confident I can perform
the cure—

Don't worry, I know you can do it. You were helped,
guided, and saved by Master Shadow. You have
what it takes now.
...Okay!
Like a flowing melody...
Transmuting murky magic...into a stream of purity...

That's right. Instead of manipulating magic to your
will, allow it to run its natural course.

Never tainting the magic's source...droplets turn
to torrents...flowing to the river...journeying to
the sea...

I...gently wave my baton, guiding that stream...
All else melts away...!
Huff...huff...
I-It worked... I...did it!

Indeed. Well done, Epsilon. Never forget what you
just experienced.
I won't, Lady Alpha!
H-Huh...?
Have you regained consciousness?
My body—it's back to normal! But I was...possessed!

Possession was the dying curse that the demon Diablos
placed on the heroes who defeated him long ago.

In other words, it is proof that a hero's blood flows
in your veins.
You mean...I'm descended from a hero?!
But...never mind that. It doesn't matter.

I've lost everything—my status, my honor, even
my will to live.
Maybe so, but you can start anew.
Start...anew?
We know the truth of this world.

We know the shadowy reality of the Cult of Diablos—
those who distort history and even seek to resurrect
the demon.

And we know what lies in the shadows of the Cult's
distorted history—the lives of those that have been
tormented by the curse.

We know how the possessed, such as yourself, have
been victims of various experiments by the Cult of
Diablos.

The Cult of Diablos?! That's a fairytale—but all
these cages... Were there victims besides me?
Two paths lie ahead of you.

You can either cling dearly to the life restored to you—
see nothing, hear nothing, act on nothing...and live
a quiet, uneventful life.

Or you can become one of us and fight the darkness
that lurks in the shadows and distorts this world.
You don’t care about my past?

If you wish to tell us, we'll listen, but is it
relevant to the life you'll now live?
...Hold on, were all of you once possessed too?
Yes. Just as you have, we lost everything.

But Shadow saved us. He taught us how to cure
the curse, a method that was likely long lost
to history.

And Shadow will lead us to the destruction of the
Cult of Diablos—that's what we're working toward.
Shadow...

It seems I owe my life not only to you, but also to
this one called "Shadow."

Then...I shall dedicate this life...this life that
would've been no more...to Shadow and to
all of you.

Welcome to the Shadow Garden. Henceforth, your name
will be Lambda.
Lambda...

We've destroyed all the surrounding hideouts
belonging to the Cult of Diablos.

Of course, this was done with great care to avoid any
association with you or the Kagenou Family.
Right... Good job, Alpha.

We've rescued many of the possessed in the process.
Most have pledged allegiance to the Shadow Garden.

The groundwork is steadily being laid for carrying
out your objective.

Wow, that's great. But if there are too many people
around, I'm not sure we can hide them all in that
village.

Regarding that, I have Zeta scouting out a new base.
We'll start moving as soon as she finds one.

Also, to coincide with the Shadow Garden's growth,
I have everyone, including the Seven Shadows,
retraining with the sword.
I see... Wait, what?!

You provided Beta and me with a thorough foundation
in swordsmanship.

But you only taught the others in the Seven Shadows
the fundamentals before encouraging them to follow
their own paths.
(Wait, hold on... Did I actually say that?!)

Thanks to your wisdom, the Seven Shadows have each
developed their individual fighting styles.

However, I thought it best to value both the secrecy
and the symbolism of the Garden.

(Ohh...I did...I totally said that! Right, Gamma and
Delta were struggling with their sword technique—)

(To be honest, I don't even wanna remember what
happened. That was the first time I experienced
any sort of setback since coming to this world.)

(Besides, Epsilon was good at controlling her magic,
Zeta excelled at anything you threw at her, and Eta...
Well, Eta pretty much had zero motivation.)

(I figured they'd sort of manage without me anyway
in their cases. I vaguely remember letting their
sword training slide after that.)
...The start of a journey with no clear path forward.

Yet...beyond that heavy mist lies the land of shadows
where we must rise!
The land of shadows...!

...Well then, if you'll excuse me. I hear your mother
scolds you if you don't show up for supper.
Pfft...!

A sword to symbolize the Shadow Garden's new base,
huh? Alpha's really got a thing for these tropes.
